interest rate; engineering fees; contractor overhead and profit; late 1991 power, fuel, labor and chemical costs.
The removal efficiencies cited in Table 3 are what is possible, and are not directly linked with the cited costs. These
costs are linked with the efficiency needed to achieve the sulfate MCL. 










